.plx | .Retard 
╰──➤ ~!! build | Logic
      ╰──➤ Logic Type | .Retard [ .bun ]
╰──➤ Argu~!! Check | STATES[ALL(local)&&( @~!! |~|~!! ncom.co/~/SDK/.!! ) 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ = NCOM | 23*@D#*!)D@U#$(DF3N!#ON#N%)!!#[BUNDLE | LCOAL] 
/!! this is the math logic that tells the device how to think and how not to screw this up. 
/!! Local Logic Chain is retained to `local Bundle` for Online & Offline state 

Math | ChainOfThought
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ query | [""]
   ╰──➤ complexity_score | 0
   ╰──➤ requires_cot | false
   ╰──➤ thinking_steps | []
   ╰──➤ final_answer | [""]
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ Argu~!!
      ╰──➤ trigger_phrases | ["explain", "why", "how does", "step by step", "analyze", "compare", "prove", "derive"]
      ╰──➤ complexity_indicators | ["multiple", "several", "relationship", "because", "therefore", "however"]
   ╰──➤ Math~!!
      ╰──➤ trigger_match_count | count(query ∩ trigger_phrases)
      ╰──➤ indicator_match_count | count(query ∩ complexity_indicators)
      ╰──➤ complexity_score | (trigger_match_count * 2) + indicator_match_count
      ╰──➤ requires_cot | complexity_score >= 2
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ inject_thinking_prompt
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ thinking_prompt | "Let me think through this step by step:\n"
         ╰──➤ format | "<thinking>{steps}</thinking>\n<answer>{answer}</answer>"
   ╰──➤ extract_steps
      ╰──➤ split_by_newline
      ╰──➤ enumerate_steps
      ╰──➤ Store~!! @thinking_steps | extracted

Math | TreeOfThought
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ root_problem | [""]
   ╰──➤ max_branches | 3
   ╰──➤ max_depth | 4
   ╰──➤ current_depth | 0
   ╰──➤ branches | []
   ╰──➤ pruned | []
   ╰──➤ best_path | []
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ generate_branches
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ parent_node | current_state
         ╰──➤ branch_prompt | "Generate {max_branches} different approaches to solve this:"
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ branches | []
         ╰──➤ i | 0
         ╰──➤ while i < max_branches
            ╰──➤ branch[i] | generate_approach(parent_node, i)
            ╰──➤ i | i + 1
      ╰──➤ Store~!! @branches | generated
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ evaluate_branches
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ scores | []
         ╰──➤ for each branch in @branches
            ╰──➤ feasibility | rate_feasibility(branch) | [0.0, 1.0]
            ╰──➤ correctness | rate_correctness(branch) | [0.0, 1.0]
            ╰──➤ efficiency | rate_efficiency(branch) | [0.0, 1.0]
            ╰──➤ score | (feasibility * 0.4) + (correctness * 0.4) + (efficiency * 0.2)
            ╰──➤ scores | append(score)
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ prune_branches
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ threshold | 0.3
         ╰──➤ for each (branch, score) in zip(@branches, @scores)
            ╰──➤ Check~!! score < threshold
               ╰──➤ @pruned | append(branch)
               ╰──➤ @branches | remove(branch)
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ select_best_path
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ best_index | argmax(@scores)
         ╰──➤ @best_path | @branches[best_index]
      ╰──➤ Check~!! @current_depth < @max_depth
         ╰──➤ current_depth | current_depth + 1
         ╰──➤ Call~!! | generate_branches(@best_path)

Math | SelfConsistency
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ problem | [""]
   ╰──➤ num_attempts | 3
   ╰──➤ temperature_range | [0.3, 0.7]
   ╰──➤ attempts | []
   ╰──➤ consensus_answer | [""]
   ╰──➤ confidence | 0.0
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ generate_attempts
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ i | 0
         ╰──➤ temp_step | (temperature_range[1] - temperature_range[0]) / num_attempts
         ╰──➤ while i < num_attempts
            ╰──➤ temperature | temperature_range[0] + (temp_step * i)
            ╰──➤ attempt[i] | solve(problem, temperature)
            ╰──➤ i | i + 1
      ╰──➤ Store~!! @attempts | generated
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ find_consensus
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ answer_counts | {}
         ╰──➤ for each attempt in @attempts
            ╰──➤ normalized | normalize_answer(attempt)
            ╰──➤ answer_counts[normalized] | answer_counts[normalized] + 1 | 0
         ╰──➤ consensus_answer | argmax(answer_counts)
         ╰──➤ confidence | max(answer_counts.values()) / num_attempts

Math | LogicalOperations
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ propositions | []
   ╰──➤ operators | ["AND", "OR", "NOT", "XOR", "IMPLIES", "IFF"]
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ evaluate
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ | A ∧ B | true if A and B are both true
         ╰──➤ | A ∨ B | true if A or B is true
         ╰──➤ | ¬A | true if A is false
         ╰──➤ | A ⊕ B | true if exactly one of A, B is true
         ╰──➤ | A → B | true if A is false or B is true
         ╰──➤ | A ↔ B | true if A and B have same truth value
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ modus_ponens
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ premise_1 | "A → B" | if A then B
         ╰──➤ premise_2 | "A" | A is true
         ╰──➤ conclusion | "B" | therefore B
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ Check~!! (A → B) ∧ A
            ╰──➤ valid | true
            ╰──➤ return B
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ modus_tollens
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ premise_1 | "A → B" | if A then B
         ╰──➤ premise_2 | "¬B" | B is false
         ╰──➤ conclusion | "¬A" | therefore not A
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ Check~!! (A → B) ∧ ¬B
            ╰──➤ valid | true
            ╰──➤ return ¬A

Math | MathOperations
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ precision | 15
   ╰──➤ overflow_check | true
   ╰──➤ underflow_check | true
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ safe_add
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ Argu~!!
            ╰──➤ a | 0
            ╰──➤ b | 0
         ╰──➤ Check~!! a + b <= MAX_VALUE
            ╰──➤ result | a + b
   ╰──➤ safe_multiply
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ Argu~!!
            ╰──➤ a | 0
            ╰──➤ b | 0
         ╰──➤ Check~!! a * b <= MAX_VALUE
            ╰──➤ result | a * b
   ╰──➤ safe_divide
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ Argu~!!
            ╰──➤ a | 0
            ╰──➤ b | 0
         ╰──➤ Check~!! b != 0
            ╰──➤ result | a / b
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ symbolic_solve
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ equation | [""]
         ╰──➤ variable | "x"
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ parse_equation
         ╰──➤ isolate_variable
         ╰──➤ simplify_expression
         ╰──➤ return solution

Math | ZeroTrustValidation
╰──➤ Argu~!!
   ╰──➤ input | [""]
   ╰──➤ expected_type | ["number", "boolean", "string", "array", "object"]
   ╰──➤ constraints | []
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ validate_type
      ╰──➤ Check~!! | typeof(input) == expected_type
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ validate_range
      ╰──➤ Argu~!!
         ╰──➤ min | -Infinity
         ╰──➤ max | Infinity
      ╰──➤ Check~!! | input >= min AND input <= max
╰──➤ Logic~!!
   ╰──➤ validate_constraints
      ╰──➤ Math~!!
         ╰──➤ for each constraint in @constraints
            ╰──➤ Check~!! | constraint(input) == true
